2. Interpretation
In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires—
"Appeals Board" means the Board appointed under section 6(1);
"Defence Council" means the Defence Council established under section 22 of the Botswana Defence Force Act (Cap. 21:05);
"medical practitioner" has the same meaning assigned to it under the Botswana Health Professions Act (Cap. 61:02); and
"military veteran" means a person who—
( a ) has completed his or her service in the Botswana Defence Force;
( b ) has completed his or her military training and is no longer serving on account of resignation; or
( c ) could not complete his or her military service or training due to injuries sustained during military service or training, or a disease contracted during or associated with military service or training.

3. Benefits relating to military veterans
The benefits relating to a military veteran shall be as follows—
